Decisive robot is a web application that chooses for you when you are feeling indecisive.
See http://decisiverobot.com/ and http://twitter.com/decisiverobot

Copyright 2012 Daniel Kinsman.

To build use GNU Make (http://www.gnu.org/software/make/).

Other prerequisites needed include:
-python 2.7
-flask (http://flask.pocoo.org/)
-coffeescript (http://coffeescript.org/)
-python twitter tools (http://mike.verdone.ca/twitter/)

Useful but not required:
-foreman (http://blog.daviddollar.org/2011/05/06/introducing-foreman.html)
-gunicorn (http://gunicorn.org/)

Once built, run web.py (or use foreman start) and open http://localhost:5000/ in a browser.
You can also run the twitter bot via twitterbot.py (after changing the "replacethis" constants in that file).

Enjoy.